  "description": {
    "en": "A flowering plant whose rhizome (underground stem) is widely used as a spice and in traditional medicine. Native to Southeast Asia, it is now cultivated throughout the tropics and subtropics.",
    "zh-Hant": "多年生草本植物，其根莖廣泛用作香料和中藥。原產於東南亞，現於熱帶和亞熱帶地區廣泛栽培。"
  },
  "habitat": {
    "en": "Warm, humid tropical and subtropical regions. Thrives in well-drained, fertile soil with partial shade."
  },
  "origin": {
    "en": "Southeast Asia, likely the Indo-Malayan region. Cultivated for over 5,000 years."
  },
  "geographicalDistribution": {
    "en": "Widely cultivated in India, China, Nigeria, Indonesia, Bangladesh, Thailand, Philippines, Jamaica, and other tropical regions."
  },
